article.description: Anthony Livingston scored 22 points, including six in overtime, and grabbed 12 rebounds, and Arkansas State beat Georgia State 75-69 Thursday night.
article.headline: Arkansas State beats Georgia State 75-69 in overtime
article.linkText: Arkansas State beats Georgia State 75-69 in overtime
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. -- Anthony Livingston scored 22 points, including six in overtime, and grabbed 12 rebounds, and Arkansas State beat Georgia State 75-69 Thursday night. Livingston and Devin Carter, who finished with 15 points, combined for 13 of the Red Wolves' 18 points in overtime with Livingston's bucket with 35 seconds left making it 71-64. Charles Waters added 13 points and 10 rebounds and Sean Gardner also scored 13 points for Arkansas State (10-10, 6-3 Sun Belt). Frederic Dure and Waters scored in the final 17 seconds of regulation to give Arkansas State a 57-56 lead, its first since early in the first half, but Isaiah Williams tied it by making 1 of 2 free throws with seven seconds left. Jeremy Hollowell scored 15 points to lead the Panthers (12-6, 5-4) before fouling out with over seven minutes left. Kevin Ware added 14 points and Markus Crider 11 while T.J. Shipes had 11 rebounds.
